INSERT INTO `assignments` VALUES (217, '17120006', 37, 2018, 1, 3, 24, NULL, 'M3 TL3 Assignment', '\r\nUnit: Interactive lecture\r\n\r\nFaculty: Manzare Shamim\r\n\r\nAssignments :\r\n1. A professor of surgery was giving a lecture on ‘burn’ in an undergraduate medical class. He started with the definition of ‘burn’ using a PowerPoint slide. The students near the back of the class seemed uninterested in the topic and were gossiping. The professor tried to attract their attention, but it created uproar in the class itself. To calm the class, he used a blank slide and asked the class to volunteer in defining ‘burn’. It brought a complete silence. Perplexed, he went to his next slide that showed a burning Rohingya village in Myanmar.\r\n\r\nAnswer the following questions considering the above scenario:                             4+4+4+(2+4)=18\r\ni) Was there anything wrong with showing the definition of the slide? Explain.\r\nii) If you are asked to run the class, how would you plan to begin?\r\niii) How could the professor have dealt with the situation at the back of the class?\r\niv) Was showing the burning village OK? Justify your comment, \r\n        and outline how you would like to use a photograph in such a class.\r\n\r\n2. Can an ‘interactive lecture’ be implemented in a class of 150 students?\r\nWhat is a ‘one-minute question’?\r\nExplain with an example how such a question can be utilized as an interaction technique in a lecture class.                                                                                                                                2+5+7+14\r\n\r\n3. Create one dialogue that would be helpful in initiating interaction and one that would hamper interaction (in Bangla or in English).                                                                                                  4+4=8\r\n', '2018-04-10 09:08:47', '40', NULL, NULL, '', 'P');
