r\n\r\n<br></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpFirst\" xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>1.<span xss=removed>    \r\n</span></span></span><span xss=removed>This\r\ncurriculum is based on– </span></p><p>\r\n\r\n<br></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>a.<span xss=removed>     </span></span></span><b xss=removed><span xss=removed>Identification of needs</span></b><span xss=removed> according to Wiseman approach, a study of error in practice,\r\ncritical incident studies in community.</span></p><p>\r\n\r\n<br></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>b.<span xss=removed>     </span></span></span><b xss=removed><span xss=removed>Elaborate aims & objectives</span></b><span xss=removed> are described according to need analysis<span xss=removed>  </span>and according to national goal. For example –\r\nBMDC curriculum to produce doctors who are able to fulfill community needs.</span></p><p>\r\n\r\n<br></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>c.<span xss=removed>      </span></span></span><b xss=removed><span xss=removed>Contents of this curriculum</span></b><span xss=removed> directly contributes to the course objectives, building\r\nblock equip the students with skill or knowledge needed tackle in later part of\r\ncourse & allow students to develop intellectual abilities such as critical\r\nthinking.</span></p><p>\r\n\r\n<br></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>d.<span xss=removed>     </span></span></span><b xss=removed><span xss=removed>Organization of contents in this curriculum</span></b><span xss=removed> in such a way that there is\r\nrevisiting of topics throughout the course at many levels of difficulty by\r\nintegration.</span></p><p>\r\n\r\n<br></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>e.<span xss=removed>     </span></span></span><b xss=removed><span xss=removed>Educational strategies </span></b><span xss=removed>are based on both student & teacher centered, problem\r\nbased & information gathering, community oriented & hospital based,\r\nintegrated & systematic.</span></p><p>\r\n\r\n<br></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>f.<span xss=removed>       </span></span></span><b xss=removed><span xss=removed>Teaching methods </span></b><span xss=removed>include both small & large groups, face to face interactive lecture\r\nand individual learning.</span></p><p>\r\n\r\n<br></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>g.<span xss=removed>      </span></span></span><span xss=removed>Both students & course are <b xss=removed>assessed</b> and choice of method depends\r\nupon objectives, local facilities available & experience of local staff.\r\nAssessment is done by MCQ, OSPE, OSCE, written, viva, practical, clinical.</span></p><p>\r\n\r\n<br></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>h.<span xss=removed>     </span></span></span><span xss=removed>Details of the curriculum is <b xss=removed>communicated</b> by preparing syllabus,\r\nstudy guide.</span></p><p>\r\n\r\n<br></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>i.<span xss=removed>       </span></span></span><span xss=removed>An ambient, cooperative <b xss=removed>educational<span xss=removed> \r\n</span>environment</b> among student & staff is maintained.</span></p><p>\r\n\r\n<br></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>j.<span xss=removed>       </span></span></span><span xss=removed>All the process be <b xss=removed>managed & maintained</b> by students,\r\nteachers, elected representatives.</span></p><p>\r\n\r\n<br></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>2.<span xss=removed>    \r\n</span></span></span><span xss=removed>This\r\ncurriculum provides a lot of development in medical education.</span></p><p>\r\n\r\n<br></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>3.<span xss=removed>    \r\n</span></span></span><span xss=removed>Time\r\ntable & duration of course of this curriculum is appropriate.</span></p><p>\r\n\r\n<br></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpLast\" xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>4.<span xss=removed>    \r\n</span></span></span><span xss=removed>Details,\r\nelaborate & easy way approach among students, teachers, staff etc were maintained.</span></p><p>\r\n\r\n<br></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" xss=removed><b xss=removed><u><span xss=removed>Weaknesses</span></u></b></p><p>\r\n\r\n<br></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpFirst\" xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>1.<span xss=removed>    \r\n</span></span></span><b xss=removed><span xss=removed>Objectives</span></b><span xss=removed> are too much , descriptive &\r\nmore informative.</span></p><p>\r\n\r\n<br></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>2.<span xss=removed>    \r\n</span></span></span><b xss=removed><span xss=removed>Identification of needs</span></b><span xss=removed> in each discipline senior teachers /\r\npractitioners may have little knowledge or absent in the day of curriculum\r\nplanning.</span></p><p>\r\n\r\n<br></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>3.<span xss=removed>    \r\n</span></span></span><b xss=removed><span xss=removed>Contents of curriculum </span></b><span xss=removed>sometimes too much (i.e.-knowledge of\r\nMRCP in MBBS students) or sometimes less ( Little about USG).</span></p><p>\r\n\r\n<br></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>4.<span xss=removed>    \r\n</span></span></span><b xss=removed><span xss=removed>Organization of content </span></b><span xss=removed>– 2<sup>nd</sup> & 3<sup>rd</sup>\r\nphase was separated. So without knowledge of pathology & microbiology\r\nstudent has placement in clinical ward. </span></p><p>\r\n\r\n<br></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>5.<span xss=removed>    \r\n</span></span></span><b xss=removed><span xss=removed>Educational strategies</span></b><span xss=removed> is not fully SPICES oriented. No\r\nelectives in this curriculum.</span></p><p>\r\n\r\n<br></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" xss=removed><b xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>6.<span xss=removed>     </span></span></span></b><b xss=removed><span xss=removed>In teaching methods </span></b><span xss=removed>sometimes group study may not possible due to lack of proper space. Due\r\nto lack of instruments sometimes individual learning is difficult.</span></p><p>\r\n\r\n<br></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>7.<span xss=removed>    \r\n</span></span></span><b xss=removed><span xss=removed>Proper assessment of students &\r\ncourse </span></b><span xss=removed>may not be\r\npossible due to large number of students, lengthy process of examination, improper\r\ntraining of teacher. Extensive long structures viva in all professional\r\nexaminations still exists.</span></p><p>\r\n\r\n<br></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" xss=removed><b xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>8.<span xss=removed>     </span></span></span></b><b xss=removed><span xss=removed>Communication of curriculum </span></b><span xss=removed>to the students, teachers, staff, dean & others were\r\npoor. So they have very little knowledge about curriculum.</span></p><p>\r\n\r\n<br></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>9.<span xss=removed>    \r\n</span></span></span><span xss=removed>Due\r\nto unavoidable sounds from outside sometimes ambient <b xss=removed>educational environment</b> is not possible.</span></p><p>\r\n\r\n<br></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>10.<span xss=removed>  </span></span></span><span xss=removed>All the process may not be <b xss=removed>managed & maintained</b> by students,\r\nteachers, staff as they do not know it.</span></p><p>\r\n\r\n<br></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>11.<span xss=removed>  </span></span></span><span xss=removed>There is no hidden curriculum.</span></p><p>\r\n\r\n<br></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpLast\" xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>12.<span xss=removed>  </span></span></span><span xss=removed>Students have little involvement in\r\ncurriculum planning.</span></p><p>\r\n\r\n<br></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" xss=removed><b xss=removed><u><span xss=removed>How to improve</span></u></b></p><p>\r\n\r\n<br></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpFirst\" xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>1.<span xss=removed>    \r\n</span></span></span><span xss=removed>All\r\nstaff, teachers, dean & faculty should be trained up.</span></p><p>\r\n\r\n<br></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>2.<span xss=removed>    \r\n</span></span></span><span xss=removed>Communication\r\nincreases by giving BMDC curriculum to every students, staff, teachers &\r\nrelevant others.</span></p><p>\r\n\r\n<br></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>3.<span xss=removed>    \r\n</span></span></span><span xss=removed>Every\r\nrelevant person may know about the medical education.</span></p><p>\r\n\r\n<br></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>4.<span xss=removed>    \r\n</span></span></span><span xss=removed>Basic\r\nprinciple of teaching should be known by teachers.</span></p><p>\r\n\r\n<br></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>5.<span xss=removed>    \r\n</span></span></span><span xss=removed>2<sup>nd</sup>\r\n& 3<sup>rd</sup> phase of MBBS course curriculum may be joined together.</span></p><p>\r\n\r\n<br></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>6.<span xss=removed>    \r\n</span></span></span><span xss=removed>Objective\r\nmay be in short & less descriptive.</span></p><p>\r\n\r\n<br></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>7.<span xss=removed>    \r\n</span></span></span><span xss=removed>Opinion\r\nof students may involve in curriculum planning.</span></p><p>\r\n\r\n<br></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>8.<span xss=removed>    \r\n</span></span></span><span xss=removed>Students\r\nmay have more knowledge about Ultrasonogram.</span></p><p>\r\n\r\n<br></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>9.<span xss=removed>    \r\n</span></span></span><span xss=removed>Problem\r\nbased, integrated, electives, systematic strategy may be applied.</span></p><p>\r\n\r\n<br></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>10.<span xss=removed>  </span></span></span><span xss=removed>Extensive long viva procedure may be\r\nconverted into objective structured practical / clinical examinations\r\n(OSPE/OSCE).</span></p><p>\r\n\r\n<br></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpLast\" xss=removed><span xss=removed> </span></p><p>\r\n\r\n<br></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" xss=removed><b xss=removed><u><span xss=removed>How to implement</span></u></b></p><p>\r\n\r\n<br></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpFirst\" xss=removed><b xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>1.<span xss=removed>     </span></span></span></b><span xss=removed>The curriculum is not a constant\r\ncomponent must be reviewed time to time. So regular discussion among teachers,\r\nstudents, staff, faculty is mandatory.</span></p><p>\r\n\r\n<br></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" xss=removed><b xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>2.<span xss=removed>     </span></span></span></b><span xss=removed>Dialogue & criticism about\r\nstrategies among each other is necessary.</span></p><p>\r\n\r\n<br></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" xss=removed><b xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>3.<span xss=removed>     </span></span></span></b><span xss=removed>Faculty, teachers must be trained up.</span></p><p>\r\n\r\n<br></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpLast\" xss=removed><span xss=removed> </span></p><p>\r\n\r\n<br></p>', '2018-01-18 08:51:56', 'upload/attachment/2cece7ed49a9737d4f51a0c298b5735b.docx', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
