ducation</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" xss=removed align=\"center\"><span xss=removed>Unit name:\r\nCurriculum development</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" xss=removed align=\"center\"><span xss=removed>Unit Code:\r\nCl 1</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" xss=removed align=\"center\"> </p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" xss=removed align=\"center\"> </p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" xss=removed align=\"center\"> </p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" xss=removed align=\"center\">Submitted by-</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" xss=removed align=\"center\"> </p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" xss=removed align=\"center\"><b xss=removed>Muhammad\r\nAbdur Rahim</b></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" xss=removed align=\"center\">Email: <a href=\"mailto:muradrahim23@yahoo.com\"><span xss=removed>muradrahim23@yahoo.com</span></a></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" xss=removed><span xss=removed>                                                                 </span>Cell:\r\n+8801674534500, +8801741009000<span xss=removed>             </span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" xss=removed> </p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" xss=removed> </p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" xss=removed align=\"center\">Faculty\r\ninformation-</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" xss=removed align=\"center\"><b xss=removed> </b></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" xss=removed align=\"center\"><b xss=removed> </b></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" xss=removed align=\"center\"><b xss=removed>Prof. Abid Hossain Mollah</b></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" xss=removed align=\"center\">Email:\r\n<a href=\"mailto:professorahm@yahoo.com\"><span xss=removed>professorahm@yahoo.com</span></a></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" xss=removed align=\"center\">Cell:\r\n+8801711530323</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span xss=removed> </span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span xss=removed> </span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span xss=removed> </span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span xss=removed> </span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span xss=removed>Title:\r\nIdentification of strengths and weaknesses of current MBBS curriculum in\r\nNephrology and ways of improving and implementation of these weaknesses in\r\ncurrent situation</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span xss=removed>Objectives:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<ol xss=removed start=\"1\" type=\"1\"><li class=\"MsoNormal\" xss=removed>Evaluation of current MBBS curriculum in\r\n     nephrology</li><li class=\"MsoNormal\" xss=removed>Ways of improvement and implementation of\r\n     suggestions for further development</li></ol>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"> </p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span xss=removed>Introduction:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Curriculum is the blueprint that entails the goals of any\r\neducational activity and endeavor to achieve the goal. It is known that ten\r\nbasic questions need to be considered before planning the curriculum and there\r\nremain five aspects of a curriculum. There should be a core and electives.\r\nDepending up on these basic facts in curriculum, the existing MBBS curriculum is\r\nevaluated and an attempt is made to further improve it.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span xss=removed>Given/current\r\ncurriculum:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">In the 2012 curriculum, in urinary system there remain five\r\ntopics namely glomerulonephritis, nephrotic syndrome, acute kidney injury,\r\nchronic kidney disease and urinary tract infection and the set learning objectives\r\nare there. Integrated teaching included rheumatic fever, glomerulonephritis and\r\nnephrotic syndrome.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span xss=removed>Overall\r\nstrength:</span> </p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Bangladesh Medical and Dental Council (BMDC) is having a\r\ncurriculum with its defined learning objectives. May it not be flaw-less, but\r\nits presence and practice is important.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Now the evaluation of nephrology part in detail is presented.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span xss=removed>Need assessment:</span>\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">The current curriculum is sufficiently justified in\r\nfulfilling the community needs. It encompassed the common renal diseases\r\nidentifiable in community that may be treated in primary care and some patients\r\nwill require secondary and tertiary care level services. Still there should be\r\na room for further improvements in need assessment especially by critical\r\nincident studies for example star fruit (kamranga) can cause acute kidney\r\ninjury. So, it might be included in future that common edible agents with\r\nnephrotoxic potentials.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span xss=removed> </span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span xss=removed> </span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span xss=removed>Aims and\r\nobjectives:</span> </p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">In the existing curriculum, the objectives are clearly\r\nmentioned. So, there is very little, if any, to improve in this area, rather to\r\nme, there remain some areas of specialists’ concern like arterio-venous\r\nfistula, renal allografts etc. which, probably might not be in core rather\r\nshould be in electives.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span xss=removed>Contents:</span>\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">The contents of existing curriculum included acute kidney\r\ninjury, chronic kidney disease, glomerulonephritis, nephrotic syndrome and\r\nurinary tract infection. These broad areas of renal diseases are quiet\r\nsufficient to address the community needs. </p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span xss=removed>Organization\r\nof contents:</span> </p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Because of the vertical organization of current curriculum,\r\nclinically relevant basic subjects are incorporated in first two academic\r\nyears, then in fourth year students are to learn para-clinical subjects. If a\r\nhorizontal integration could be made especially in to topics like\r\npost-streptococcal glomerulonephritis and urinary tract infections to involve\r\nmedicine, nephrology, paediatrics, patology, microbiology, pharmacology,\r\ncommunity medicine in integrated teaching, definitely it could achieve a better\r\nlearning outcome.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span xss=removed>Educational\r\nstrategies:</span> </p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Regarding the educational strategies, there is very little\r\nin writing. This appears to be of discipline based and opportunistic. If\r\ndirection is given towards problem based and integrated, then it would be\r\nbetter.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span xss=removed>Teaching\r\nmethods to be used: </span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Little is known from the existing, 2012 undergraduate\r\nmedical curriculum, regarding use of teaching methods. If broad areas of\r\nnephrology in this curriculum are to be evaluated, all 5 topics are for large\r\ngroup teaching especially lectures (5 hours). So, definitely power-point\r\npresentation is to be used. If we consider the learning objectives, then small\r\ngroup teaching at bed side by demonstrating the real patient would result in\r\nbetter learning outcome.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span xss=removed>Assessment:</span>\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Very little is extracted from the current curriculum\r\nregarding assessment in nephrology except one Item in card 1. If a clear\r\ndistribution in assessment might be made like topics to be covered in bed side clinical\r\nexamination for example nephrotic syndrome, chronic kidney disease and theory\r\nlike anaemia management of chronic kidney disease etc.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span xss=removed> </span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span xss=removed> </span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span xss=removed>Communication\r\nof the curriculum:</span> </p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">There is an existing curriculum but is poorly communicated\r\nto all (if any) clinical teachers and students of respective course. It is\r\nprobably because of ignorance of the presence of curriculum by many clinical\r\nteachers. Many clinical staffs do not know how much is to teach to a 3<sup>rd</sup>\r\nyear clinical placement or a 5<sup>th</sup> year clinical placement. Students\r\ndo not know the existence of the curriculum. So, this communication should be\r\nemphasized for both teachers and students to attain a better learning outcome.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span xss=removed>Educational\r\nenvironment:</span> </p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">In resource-constrain setting like ours, the appropriate\r\nattainment of an appropriate educational environment is often impossible. During\r\na bedside teaching, it is almost impossible to create a calm environment. It is\r\nquiet impossible to give proper attention to 24-30 students, or supervise or\r\nteach examination techniques/skills to all students in a single 2 hour clinical\r\nclass. </p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span xss=removed>Management\r\nof the overall process:</span> </p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">In the light of five basic aspects of curriculum namely\r\naims, content, organization of contents, learning methods and assessment, the\r\n2012 undergraduate medical curriculum encompassing nephrology addressed almost\r\nall areas. But, there are weaknesses in descriptions of learning methods to be\r\nused for given tasks and ways of assessment. A better description in these\r\nareas is likely to bring about an expected learning outcome.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span xss=removed>Conclusion:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Curriculum is a dynamic theme. Always there remains a scope\r\nfor improvement. The overall weakness of the curriculum is the inadequacy in given\r\ntime for development of communication skills, lack of evaluation and feedback\r\nby the students regarding the course and teachers. For implementation of the newly\r\n(in this assignment) proposed activities, a subject committee may be formed to\r\nidentify areas for further improvement. These proposals might be communicated\r\nwith the medicine department and phase 3 meetings. Ultimately at national level,\r\nduring curriculum development, these issues should be raised and incorporated (if\r\nfound logical by arguments) in undergraduate medical curriculum.</p>\r\n\r\n', '2018-01-19 12:49:04', 'upload/attachment/29c9d51121409bca4e7335a7b3f5f558.doc', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
