INSERT INTO `assignments_reply` VALUES (66, 35, 'Assignment ', 'A. Importance of Learning Objectives in Educational Program\r\nI. Introduction\r\nIn educational program learning objectives are brief statements that describes what students will be expected to learn by the end of study year, course, unit lesson, project or class period. It is the cornerstone of instructional technology, precise and detail, relates to one aspect of area. All learners need to know what is expected of them – in other words they need to be informed of learning outcomes/objectives. Once the contents to be included in a lesson have been decided by need assessment, task analysis, curricular guides or other materials, the next step is to develop, write or select the objectives which will comprise of the unit of instructions. \r\nII. Importance\r\n“Remember that if you don’t know where you are going, you can’t know how to get there.” The statement stresses the importance of learning outcome. Selection of learning objectives are important in every aspect of teaching learning process. \r\n• Objectives contribute to instructional process in the following ways:\r\n It provides direction for the instructor and it clearly conveys his instructional intent to others. \r\n It provides a guide for selecting the subject matter, the teaching method and the materials to be used during instructions. \r\n It provides a guide for constructing test and other instruments for evaluating student achievement. \r\n• Learning objective tell students what is important: \r\nWithout learning objectives it is difficult for students to know what they are supposed to be learning. In a lecture, teacher can talk extensively about a case but unless he or she states explicitly, it can be difficult for students to know where to direct their attention. Do they need to know the details of that specific case or what principles are they supposed to glean from the example? Students can waste a great deal of time studying the things that are not necessary, to the detriment of their learning as a whole. The uncertainty also cause unnecessary anxiety.  \r\n• Learning objectives enable good assessment development:\r\nEach year as we write our assessments we should go through the learning objectives and make sure their assessed. In this way, the assessment becomes fair and applied to the course. \r\n• Learning objectives encourage reflection and good course design and development:\r\nDevelopment is an intrinsic part of medicine. Knowledge has grown rapidly over the last fifty years, new skill have become a routine part of practice and old skills have become redundant. As instructors write and review the learning objectives in a course, they can identify the level of learning that is specified in each. At an entry level course it is acceptable to have a number of lower level learning objectives. However, there needs to be some serious thinking done if a post-graduate course is not mainly made up of higher level learning objectives. The use of learning objectives linked with assessment design helps us to identify the background knowledge that we assume students have.  \r\n• Learning objectives promotes equity and reduces unnecessary stress:\r\nLearning objectives help reduce the ‘gaming’ aspects that can proliferate in the absence of clear information. \r\n\r\nIII. Conclusion\r\nThe derivation, development, organization and formulation of objectives are among the most difficult of the educational tasks a faculty must performed. Unless this work is done, the effort invested in teaching learning process represents long journey with neither compass nor map. \r\n\r\nB. Importance of Taxonomy in Educational Program\r\nI. Introduction\r\nTaxonomy is as old as the language skill of the mankind. Taxonomy is important because it allows us to represent the evolution of living organisms expose the differences and similarities between them. The taxonomy of educational objectives is intended to provide for classification of the goals of the educational system. Although the specific learning outcomes resulting from a course of study may run into hundreds, most of them can be classified under a small number of headings. One of the most important aim in post primary education is the attainment of critical or higher order thinking skills. Identifying how to encourage, teach and then assess their skills is important. Taxonomy of educational objectives is regarded as a tool for such.  \r\nII. Importance\r\n• Taxonomy is a language for communication, and essential infrastructure for other activities in society. Lack of good taxonomy and skilled taxonomists is an impediment for society. If a researcher does not have a reliable name on his/her study object, it is impossible to communicate and publish on the results.  If the taxonomy is poor studies may be conducted on different texa but reported by the same name create confusion. It is an essential infrastructure for other fields. \r\n• Taxonomy serves several useful purposes: \r\n Indicates the type of learning outcomes that should be considered.\r\n Provides a framework for classifying those outcomes. \r\n Directs attention towards changes in student performance in variety of areas \r\n Useful in designing a lesson plan and can be used to adopt a previously designed lesson\r\n Forms the blueprint for forming the assessment tools- taxonomy can help by providing lists of competencies available and in setting an appropriate level of performance.\r\n Asking questions at different taxonomic levels.\r\n Increasing the cognitive levels of activity.\r\n Provides common grounds and makes comparison of various teaching program easier. \r\n\r\nIII. Conclusion\r\nTo determine the standard to which the student will full-fill the learning outcome hierarchies of the taxonomy is important assessment tool. \r\n\r\nC. Specific Objectives on the Topic –“The Penis” According to the Hierarchies in Each Learning Domain\r\n\r\n1. Knowledge:\r\n• Define phimosis.\r\n• Explain the causes of UTI in phimosis.\r\n• Describe the steps of management of a boy with UTI for circumcision. \r\n• Choose the best technic for circumcision in phimosis.\r\n• Rationale the superiority of dissection method over guillotine method of circumcision.\r\n2. Skill: \r\n• Make a preoperative checklist for circumcision.\r\n• Position the boy on the operation table for circumcision.\r\n• Make a list of instruments for circumcision. \r\n• Enumerate the steps of circumcision.\r\n• Demonstrate the management of urethral injury during circumcision.  \r\n3. Attitude:\r\n• Put the points to be monitored in a boy after circumcision in the post-operative room\r\n• Identify the signs of a subcutaneous hematoma following circumcision.\r\n• Counsel the parents of a boy with reactionary hemorrhage following circumcision.\r\n• Not the immediate measures to control post-operative hemorrhage following circumcision.\r\n• Describes the measures to be taken to prevent recurrence of hemorrhage. \r\n\r\n\r\n', '2018-01-27 19:21:57', 'upload/attachment/f0679b3f8cbea1d99f20e4c9327149ff.docx', '<p>Thanks for the answers for the task. I have gone through your assignments but few suggestions</p><p>a) Importance of taxonomy and learning objectives are more or less ok. </p><p>b) Learning objectives, better to write in a way what the learner should be able to do at the end of a learning period that they could not do beforehand. Here selection of appropriate action verbs are very important</p><p>e.g. as from your statement, what is phimosis</p><p>Learning objective: At the end of the session, the student will be able to <span xss=removed><b>define</b></span> phimosis.</p><p>At the end of this session, the learners will be able to <b><span xss=removed>prepare </span></b>a trolly for circumcision. These define, prepare are action verbs, but again you need to think, are these measurable?</p><p>c) You did not mention anything about 3 hierarchies in each learning domain and 5 learning capabilities that human can learn<br></p>', NULL, '2018-01-28 07:21:57', 'F');
INSERT INTO `assignments_reply` VALUES (67, 31, 'Educational objectives and competencies', 'Importance of educational objectives and taxonomy and 5 specific objectives on any topic of my specialty according to the hierarchies in each learning domain.', '2018-01-31 01:37:23', 'upload/attachment/720978c660f836ddb6afa42712678497.docx', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><o> </o></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraph\" xss=removed>&lt;!--[if !supportLists]--&gt;A.<span xss=removed>     \r\n</span>&lt;!--[endif]--&gt;Understanding the definition: Satisfactory\r\n(which you have described in the introduction)</p><p class=\"MsoNormal\">Importance of Toxonomy & objectives:</p><p class=\"MsoNormal\">Your write up is Ok. But the fact that understanding of\r\ntheir importance is very much necessary for its future practical use by youself.\r\nIt would be better if you have written their importance in your own language or\r\nwith example.</p><p class=\"MsoNormal\">Your write up of objectives:</p><p class=\"MsoNormal\">1. The form the writing objectives which is to be followed. </p><p class=\"MsoNormal\">e.g.</p><p class=\"MsoNormal\">At the end of the class 4<sup>th</sup>yr MBBS class students\r\nwill be able to:</p><p class=\"MsoNormal\">- describe the pathology of appendicitis (as you have\r\nmentioned pathology and causes: - it is better to keep them simple and\r\nspecific. So use only one thing at a time). <a name=\"_GoBack\"></a></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\">2. Verb is OK.</p><p class=\"MsoNormal\">3. Application: <b>Demonstrate</b>\r\nis a verb used in <b>psychomotor domain (skill)</b>.</p><p class=\"MsoNormal\">It would be :…………. able to <b>relate </b>the cause of pain in it …………………..    (or around the umbilicus) in appendicitis.</p><p class=\"MsoNormal\">4. OK. </p><p class=\"MsoNormal\">5. So, the verb could be: <b>compose</b> the differential diagnosis of acute appendicitis.</p><p class=\"MsoNormal\">6. OK</p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b><i>NB. You have not used criteria in any of the objectives. <o></o></i></b></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\">B. Psychomotor domain</p><p class=\"MsoNormal\">1. Perception level – here the student will follow your\r\ninstruction.</p><p class=\"MsoNormal\">So it could be written: </p><p class=\"MsoNormal\">Write/describe the steps of appendicitis as demonstrated the\r\nby teacher</p><p class=\"MsoNormal\">c) Affective domain:</p><p class=\"MsoNormal\">1. Receiving : The verb aware of is not measurable</p><p class=\"MsoNormal\">It could be : “describe the feeling of the patient”.</p><p class=\"MsoNormal\">2. Responding ……… Answer the queries of the patient </p><p class=\"MsoNormal\">3. Valuing….persuade the patient about the importance\r\nsurgery. </p><p class=\"MsoNormal\">4. Organise : OK. classify the urgency of an Emergency surgery\r\nto the patient.</p><p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</p><p class=\"MsoNormal\">5. Characterization of value : Review different kinds of\r\nappendisectomy ( usually this is for PG students ot specialists)</p>', 'upload/attachment/6ec27e1ed0681441a815b120d0452adf.docx', '2018-01-31 13:37:23', 'F');
INSERT INTO `assignments_reply` VALUES (68, 51, 'Importance of taxonomy & learning objective in educational program. 5 specific objectives on RENAL FUNCTION according to the hierarchies in each learning domain', 'Sir,\r\nPlease see the attachment.', '2018-01-27 22:19:31', 'upload/attachment/f1875c990f3a17a5837e6fafad51d909.docx', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span xss=removed>Dear fellow<o></o></span></p><p xss=removed><span xss=removed>Thanks\r\nfor your much effort for preparing  assignment. I have some observation as following .<o></o></span></p><ol><li xss=removed><span xss=removed>Taxonomy\r\nusually help to classify learning objectives;setting learning experience and\r\nlearning objectives are the basis for designing curriculum,content,evaluation.<o></o></span></li><li xss=removed><span xss=removed>Every\r\nspecific objectives should have at least two things- <b>Task</b>(which\r\ninclude <u>act/action verb</u>, <u>Content</u> & <u>Condition</u>) \r\nand <b>criteria</b>. The verb \'Perform/diagnose/prepare/show\' etc can use for psycho-motor\r\ndomain; \'Respond\' may be use for affective domain,explain/describe should use for cognitive domain. In cognitive domain whether the learner satisfy/encourage/take safety\r\nmeasure.<o></o></span></li><li xss=removed><span xss=removed>Please\r\nrewrite accordingly and submit today. you should also mention your name/ID\r\nno.<o></o></span></li></ol><p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</p><p xss=removed><span xss=removed>Prof\r\nMd Shah Alam (MBBS,DTCD, MCPS, MMEd)</span></p><p xss=removed><span xss=removed>Prof & Head, Forensic Medicine</span></p><p xss=removed><span xss=removed>Ibrahim Medical College</span></p><p xss=removed><span xss=removed><o></o></span></p>', NULL, '2018-01-28 10:19:31', 'F');
