> in a chat room</span><span class=\"s10\" xss=removed>’ is one way of e-learning process where the student and faculty meet online as in lecture theatre.- an extension of face to face learning environment.</span></span></div><div class=\"s16\" xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>d. </span><span class=\"s9\" xss=removed>‘</span><span class=\"s9\" xss=removed>Formal classes in Bulletin board’</span><span class=\"s9\" xss=removed> </span><span class=\"s10\" xss=removed>is one way of online learning where student may involve in discussion panel session like SGT- an extension of face to face learning environment.</span></span></div><div class=\"s16\" xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>e. </span><span class=\"s10\" xss=removed>Audio conferencing using</span><span class=\"s9\" xss=removed> </span><span class=\"s9\" xss=removed>VoIP</span><span class=\"s10\" xss=removed>(</span><span class=\"s10\" xss=removed>Voice over internet protocol) or Teleconferencing by using Skype</span><span class=\"s10\" xss=removed>, a learner can interact with the teacher,</span><span class=\"s10\" xss=removed> is an extension of face to face learning environment.</span></span></div><div class=\"s16\" xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>f. </span><span class=\"s9\" xss=removed>Video conferencing</span><span class=\"s10\" xss=removed> and </span><span class=\"s9\" xss=removed>Web conferencing</span><span class=\"s10\" xss=removed>: Here the student and faculty can interact much as live lecture, or live SGT. Both are the examples of an extension of face to face learning </span><span class=\"s10\" xss=removed>environment</span><span class=\"s10\" xss=removed>.</span></span></div><p class=\"s12\" xss=removed><span xss=removed> </span></p><p class=\"s12\" xss=removed><span xss=removed><span class=\"s9\" xss=removed>Assignment -2:</span><span class=\"s10\" xss=removed> </span><span class=\"s9\" xss=removed>Describe the process </span><span class=\"s9\" xss=remove