span class=\"s9\" xss=removed>-</span><span class=\"s10\" xss=removed>learning activities include </span><span class=\"s9\" xss=removed>participating</span><span class=\"s9\" xss=removed> in</span><span class=\"s10\" xss=removed> </span><span class=\"s14\" xss=removed>online discussion</span><span class=\"s10\" xss=removed>,</span><span class=\"s9\" xss=removed> </span><span class=\"s14\" xss=removed>online </span><span class=\"s14\" xss=removed>chatting</span><span class=\"s10\" xss=removed>,</span><span class=\"s9\" xss=removed></span><span class=\"s14\" xss=removed>c</span><span class=\"s14\" xss=removed>onferencing</span><span class=\"s10\" xss=removed> </span><span class=\"s10\" xss=removed>(Tele-conferencing, Audio conferencing, video conferencing)</span><span class=\"s10\" xss=removed>.</span><span class=\"s10\" xss=removed>l</span></span></div><div class=\"s20\" xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>b. </span><span class=\"s10\" xss=removed>Online searching: </span><span class=\"s10\" xss=removed>Accessing e-learning content</span><span class=\"s10\" xss=removed> </span><span class=\"s10\" xss=removed>(e-journal,</span><span class=\"s10\" xss=removed> </span><span class=\"s10\" xss=removed>e-books)</span><span class=\"s10\" xss=removed>; e-portfolios; </span><span class=\"s10\" xss=removed>assessment</span><span class=\"s10\" xss=removed>;</span><span class=\"s10\" xss=removed> </span><span class=\"s10\" xss=removed>exercise</span><span class=\"s10\" xss=removed> </span><span class=\"s10\" xss=removed>to stimulate thinking</span><span class=\"s10\" xss=removed>.</span></span></div><div class=\"s20\" xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>c. </span><span class=\"s10\" xss=removed>Processing </span><span class=\"s10\" xss=removed>of offline activities</span><span class=\"s10\" xss=removed>: Interactive simulation, animation</span><span class=\"s10\" xss=removed>, DVD, Reusable learning material.</span></span></div><div class=\"s20\" xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>d. </span><span class=\"s10\" xss=removed>Instant messaging by email, </span><span class=\"s10\" xss=removed>Info</span><span class=\"s10\" xss=removed>rmal course related discussions</span><span class=\"s10\" xss=removed>.</span></span></div><p class=\"s21\" xss=removed><span xss=removed> </span></p><div class=\"s19\" xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>2. </span><span class=\"s10\" xss=removed>Process for supporting logistic & e-administration: </span></span></div><div class=\"s20\" xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>a. </span><span class=\"s10\" xss=removed>Tracking of content & participant, managing placement, timetable, exam result</span><span class=\"s10\" xss=removed>.</span><span class=\"s10\" xss=removed></span></span></div><div class=\"s20\" xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>b. </span><span class=\"s10\" xss=removed>Registration,</span><span class=\"s10\" xss=removed> f</span><span class=\"s10\" xss=removed>inancing, human resources, building etc.</span></span></div><div class=\"s20\" xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>c. </span><span class=\"s10\" xss=removed>Audit, quality assurance & compliance,</span><span class=\"s10\" xss=removed> scrutiny.</span></span></div><div class=\"s19\" xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>3. </span><span class=\"s10\" xss=removed>Process for assessment: Use of ICT for authoring, delivery, marking, feedback,</span><span class=\"s10\" xss=removed> </span><span class=\"s10\" xss=removed>analysis.</span></span></div><div class=\"s19\" xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>4. </span><span class=\"s10\" xss=removed>Process</span><span class=\"s10\" xss=removed> for community support: content creation(Wikipedia,</span><span class=\"s10\" xss=removed> </span><span class=\"s10\" xss=removed>blogging),</span><span class=\"s10\" xss=removed> </span><span class=\"s10\" xss=removed>file sharing(</span><span class=\"s10\" xss=removed>youtube</span><span class=\"s10\" xss=removed>), and discussion (face</span><span class=\"s10\" xss=removed> </span><span class=\"s10\" xss=removed>book)</span></span></div><p class=\"s8\" xss=removed><span xss=removed> </span></p><p class=\"s8\" xss=removed><font color=\"#000000\"><span xss=removed><a name=\"_GoBack\"></a><span class=\"s22\" xss=removed><span class=\"bumpedFont15\" xss=removed>Role of e-learning in CPD</span></span><span class=\"s23\" xss=removed><span class=\"bumpedFont15\" xss=removed>:</span></span><span class=\"s10\" xss=removed></span></span></font></p><p class=\"s25\" xss=removed><span xss=removed><span class=\"s24\" xss=removed>Continuing</span><span class=\"s24\" xss=removed> </span><span class=\"s24\" xss=removed>professional </span><span class=\"s24\" xss=removed>d</span><span class=\"s24\" xss=removed>evelopment (CPD)</span><span class=\"s24\" xss=removed> is a combination of approaches and</span><span class=\"s24\" xss=removed> techniques </span><span class=\"s24\" xss=removed>of </span><span class=\"s24\" xss=removed>continuous improvement</span><span class=\"s24\" xss=removed> </span><span class=\"s24\" xss=removed>of </span><span class=\"s24\" xss=removed>own learning and growth</span><span class=\"s24\" xss=removed> to keep up</span><span class=\"s24\" xss=removed>-</span><span class=\"s24\" xss=removed>to</span><span class=\"s24\" xss=removed>-</span><span class=\"s24\" xss=removed>date with current professional requirements</span><span class=\"s24\" xss=removed> </span><span class=\"s24\" xss=removed>in response to the need</span><span class=\"s24\" xss=removed> </span><span class=\"s24\" xss=removed>to</span><span class=\"s24\" xss=removed> maintain </span><span class=\"s24\" xss=removed>expertise </span><span class=\"s24\" xss=removed>post qualification. CPD is </span><span class=\"s24\" xss=removed>not restricted to formal of the job training, seminars or workshops</span><span class=\"s24\" xss=removed> but informal</span><span class=\"s24\" xss=removed> gaining of the</span><span class=\"s24\" xss=removed> knowledge and </span><span class=\"s24\" xss=removed>skill in continuous, structured, professionally focused activities.</span><span class=\"s24\" xss=removed></span></span></p><p class=\"s25\" xss=removed><span class=\"s24\" xss=removed>Traditional way of face to face course, seminars, workshop, reading journals or text, are not always possible due to workload, family commitment, travel distance, cost, lack of library service etc. </span></p><p class=\"s25\" xss=removed><span xss=removed> </span></p><p class=\"s25\" xss=removed><span xss=removed><span class=\"s10\" xss=removed>Online </span><span class=\"s10\" xss=removed>environment for </span><span class=\"s10\" xss=removed>CPD is ideally suited to meet the crisis</span><span class=\"s10\" xss=removed>. E-learning is more</span><span class=\"s10\" xss=removed> convenience,</span><span class=\"s10\" xss=removed> </span><span class=\"s10\" xss=removed>relevance, individualization</span><span class=\"s10\" xss=removed> and suitable for</span><span class=\"s10\" xss=removed> self-assessment</span><span class=\"s10\" xss=removed> &</span><span class=\"s10\" xss=removed>independent learning</span><span class=\"s10\" xss=removed>.</span><span class=\"s24\" xss=removed> </span><span class=\"s26\" xss=removed>e-learning</span><span class=\"s24\" xss=removed> </span><span class=\"s24\" xss=removed>demonstrates versatility</span><span class=\"s24\" xss=removed>, flexibility that encourage interaction to learn in own time, at own pace</span><span class=\"s24\" xss=removed> and</span><span class=\"s24\" xss=removed> in own preferred order for </span><span class=\"s24\" xss=removed>self </span><span class=\"s24\" xss=removed>growth</span><span class=\"s24\" xss=removed> by constantly updating skills to secure professionally competent and committed to his own development</span><span class=\"s24\" xss=removed>. The individual can participate in content </span><span class=\"s24\" xss=removed>creation(</span><span class=\"s24\" xss=removed>Wikipedia, blogging), file sharing(</span><span class=\"s24\" xss=removed>Youtube</span><span class=\"s24\" xss=removed>, </span><span class=\"s24\" xss=removed>Flikr,Instagram</span><span class=\"s24\" xss=removed>) and discussion(</span><span class=\"s24\" xss=removed>facebook</span><span class=\"s24\" xss=removed>, instant messaging). The individual  may involve in formal question answer session in chat room, audio conferencing on free voice over internet services(VoIP, </span><span class=\"s24\" xss=removed>skype</span><span class=\"s24\" xss=removed>), video conferencing and web conferencing by using laptop with webcam, microphones etc.</span></span></p><div xss=removed><span class=\"s24\" xss=removed><br></span></div>', NULL, '2018-02-11 15:11:23', 'F');
INSERT INTO `assignments_reply` VALUES (130, 72, 'Assignment: ‘Online environment is merely an extension of face to face learning environment’, Discuss why? Describe the process of e-learning and its role in CPD.', 'Madam,\r\n               Assalamualaikum. I received your SMS over mobile and later on your e-mail. I am extremely sorry for the delay in submitting assignment. Thank you very much for kind consideration by allowing me to submit the assignment lately. Here I am submitting it as attachment.\r\nThank you once again for your kind words.\r\nDr.Wasey', '2018-02-13 06:54:52', 'upload/attachment/681fffa20a0121d82178e4f473ba98a7.docx', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" xss=removed><b><span xss=removed>Online\r\nenvironment is merely an extension of face to face learning environment’,\r\nDiscuss why?</span></b><b><span xss=removed><o></o></span></b></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraph\" xss=removed>&lt;!--[if !supportLists]--&gt;<b><span xss=removed>1.<span xss=removed>       </span></span></b>&lt;!--[endif]--&gt;<b><span xss=removed>Introduction:<o></o></span></b></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" xss=removed><span xss=removed>Online\r\nenvironment is an educational approach, cultural context and physical setting where\r\nthe teaching & learning occur by using ICT (information & communication\r\ntechnologies). Many of the principles of face to face teaching & learning\r\nalso apply to online facilitation, such as <b>principles\r\nof facilitator’s</b> being the <u>guide</u> should allow student to work\r\nthemselves through issues instead of supplying information only; In addition\r\naddress the familiar issues of competition, conflict & responsibilities. E-learning\r\nenvironments are of two types: <b>Purely\r\nonline</b> or <b>Blended </b>(online and\r\nface-to-face). <o></o></span></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpFirst\" xss=removed>&lt;!--[if !supportLists]--&gt;<b><span xss=removed>2.<span xss=removed>       </span></span></b>&lt;!--[endif]--&gt;<b><span xss=removed>Discussion:<o></o></span></b></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" xss=removed>&lt;!--[if !supportLists]--&gt;<span xss=removed>a.<span xss=removed>      \r\n</span></span>&lt;!--[endif]--&gt;<span xss=removed>Blended e-learning is an\r\nextension of face to face learning environment, here online environment and\r\nface-to-face both are used for the learning<o></o></span></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" xss=removed>&lt;!--[if !supportLists]--&gt;<span xss=removed>b.<span xss=removed>     \r\n</span></span>&lt;!--[endif]--&gt;<span xss=removed>Problem based learning (PBL): In\r\ne-learning the PBL may be practiced either as purely <b><u>e-PBL</u></b> or <b><u>Face to\r\nface e-PBL</u></b>. <o></o></span></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" xss=removed><u><span xss=removed>Face to face e-PBL</span></u><span xss=removed>\r\nis an extension of face to face learning environment in online learning.<o></o></span></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" xss=removed>&lt;!--[if !supportLists]--&gt;<span xss=removed>c.<span xss=removed>      \r\n</span></span>&lt;!--[endif]--&gt;<b><span xss=removed>‘Synchronous\r\nformal question and answer in a chat room</span></b><span xss=removed>’ is one way of\r\ne-learning process where the student and faculty meet online as in lecture\r\ntheatre.- an extension of face to face learning environment.<o></o></span></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" xss=removed>&lt;!--[if !supportLists]--&gt;<span xss=removed>d.<span xss=removed>     \r\n</span></span>&lt;!--[endif]--&gt;<b><span xss=removed>‘Formal\r\nclasses in Bulletin board’ </span></b><span xss=removed>is one way of online learning\r\nwhere student may involve in discussion panel session like SGT- an extension of\r\nface to face learning environment.<o></o></span></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" xss=removed>&lt;!--[if !supportLists]--&gt;<span xss=removed>e.<span xss=removed>     \r\n</span></span>&lt;!--[endif]--&gt;<span xss=removed>Audio conferencing using<b> VoIP</b>(Voice over internet protocol) or\r\nTeleconferencing by using Skype, a learner can interact with the teacher, is an\r\nextension of face to face learning environment.<o></o></span></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpLast\" xss=removed>&lt;!--[if !supportLists]--&gt;<span xss=removed>f.<span xss=removed>       \r\n</span></span>&lt;!--[endif]--&gt;<b><span xss=removed>Video\r\nconferencing</span></b><span xss=removed> and <b>Web\r\nconferencing</b>: Here the student and faculty can interact much as live\r\nlecture, or live SGT. Both are the examples of an extension of face to face\r\nlearning environment.<o></o></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" xss=removed><span xss=removed> </span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" xss=removed><b><span xss=removed>Describe the process of  e-learning and its role in CPD?</span></b><span xss=removed><o></o></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" xss=removed><u><span xss=removed>Answer:</span></u><span xss=removed>\r\nProcess of e-learning are structuring the Schedules, Rules & Protocol of\r\nhuman activity involve in e-learning. E-learning contents include teaching\r\nmaterials, reference materials, materials of practice domain & guides.\r\nContents may be created & determined by teacher or student selected or\r\ncommunity supported.<o></o></span></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpFirst\" xss=removed>&lt;!--[if !supportLists]--&gt;<span xss=removed>1.<span xss=removed>       </span></span>&lt;!--[endif]--&gt;<span xss=removed>Process\r\nfor content (two types): Digital materials (websites, books, study guide,\r\nlecture slide,) and course content (syllabi/ Curricula).<o></o></span></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" xss=removed>&lt;!--[if !supportLists]--&gt;<span xss=removed>a.<span xss=removed>      \r\n</span></span>&lt;!--[endif]--&gt;<span xss=removed>Online processing for e<b>-</b>learning activities include <b>participating in</b> <u>online discussion</u>,<b> </b><u>online chatting</u>,<b> </b><u>conferencing</u> (Tele-conferencing,\r\nAudio conferencing, video conferencing).l<o></o></span></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" xss=removed>&lt;!--[if !supportLists]--&gt;<span xss=removed>b.<span xss=removed>     \r\n</span></span>&lt;!--[endif]--&gt;<span xss=removed>Online searching: Accessing\r\ne-learning content (e-journal, e-books); e-portfolios; assessment; exercise to\r\nstimulate thinking.<o></o></span></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" xss=removed>&lt;!--[if !supportLists]--&gt;<span xss=removed>c.<span xss=removed>      \r\n</span></span>&lt;!--[endif]--&gt;<span xss=removed>Processing of offline activities:\r\nInteractive simulation, animation, DVD, Reusable learning material.<o></o></span></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpLast\" xss=removed>&lt;!--[if !supportLists]--&gt;<span xss=removed>d.<span xss=removed>     \r\n</span></span>&lt;!--[endif]--&gt;<span xss=removed>Instant messaging by email, Informal\r\ncourse related discussions.<o></o></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" xss=removed><span xss=removed> </span></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpFirst\" xss=removed>&lt;!--[if !supportLists]--&gt;<span xss=removed>2.<span xss=removed>       </span></span>&lt;!--[endif]--&gt;<span xss=removed>Process\r\nfor supporting logistic & e-administration: <o></o></span></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" xss=removed>&lt;!--[if !supportLists]--&gt;<span xss=removed>a.<span xss=removed>      \r\n</span></span>&lt;!--[endif]--&gt;<span xss=removed>Tracking of content &\r\nparticipant, managing placement, timetable, exam result. <o></o></span></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" xss=removed>&lt;!--[if !supportLists]--&gt;<span xss=removed>b.<span xss=removed>     \r\n</span></span>&lt;!--[endif]--&gt;<span xss=removed>Registration, financing, human\r\nresources, building etc.<o></o></span></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" xss=removed>&lt;!--[if !supportLists]--&gt;<span xss=removed>c.<span xss=removed>      \r\n</span></span>&lt;!--[endif]--&gt;<span xss=removed>Audit, quality assurance &\r\ncompliance, scrutiny.<o></o></span></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" xss=removed>&lt;!--[if !supportLists]--&gt;<span xss=removed>3.<span xss=removed>       </span></span>&lt;!--[endif]--&gt;<span xss=removed>Process\r\nfor assessment: Use of ICT for authoring, delivery, marking, feedback, analysis.<o></o></span></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpLast\" xss=removed>&lt;!--[if !supportLists]--&gt;<span xss=removed>4.<span xss=removed>       </span></span>&lt;!--[endif]--&gt;<span xss=removed>Process\r\nfor community support: content creation(Wikipedia, blogging), file\r\nsharing(youtube), and discussion (face book)<o></o></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" xss=removed><b><span xss=removed><o> </o></span></b></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" xss=removed><b><u><span xss=removed>Role of e-learning in CPD</span></u></b><b><span xss=removed>:</span></b><span xss=removed>\r\n<o></o></span></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpFirst\" xss=removed><span xss=removed>Continuing professional development\r\n(CPD) is a combination of approaches and techniques of </span><span xss=removed>continuous improvement</span><span xss=removed> of own learning and growth</span><span xss=removed> to keep up-to-date with current\r\nprofessional requirements</span><span xss=removed>\r\nin response to the need</span><span xss=removed>\r\n</span><span xss=removed>to maintain expertise\r\n</span><span xss=removed>post qualification.\r\nCPD is not restricted to formal of the job training, seminars or workshops but\r\ninformal gaining of the knowledge and skill in continuous, structured,\r\nprofessionally focused activities. <o></o></span></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" xss=removed><span xss=removed>Traditional way of face to face course,\r\nseminars, workshop, reading journals or text, are not always possible due to\r\nworkload, family commitment, travel distance, cost, lack of library service\r\netc. <o></o></span></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" xss=removed><span xss=removed> </span></p><p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpLast\" xss=removed><span xss=removed>Online\r\nenvironment for CPD is ideally suited to meet the crisis. E-learning is more convenience,\r\nrelevance, individualization and suitable for self-assessment & independent\r\nlearning.</span><span xss=removed> <b>e-learning</b> </span><span xss=removed>demonstrates versatility, flexibility\r\nthat encourage interaction to learn in own time, at own pace and in own\r\npreferred order for self growth by constantly updating skills to secure\r\nprofessionally competent and committed to his own development. The individual\r\ncan participate in content creation(Wikipedia, blogging), file sharing(Youtube,\r\nFlikr,Instagram) and discussion(facebook, instant messaging). The\r\nindividual  may involve in formal\r\nquestion answer session in chat room, audio conferencing on free voice over\r\ninternet services(VoIP, skype), video conferencing and web conferencing by\r\nusing laptop with webcam, microphones etc.<o></o></span></p>', NULL, '2018-02-13 18:54:52', 'F');
INSERT INTO `assignments_reply` VALUES (131, 76, 'E-learning & CPD', '\"e-learning is merely an extension of face to face learning\" explain why?\r\nRole of e-learning in CPD', '2018-02-13 06:51:04', 'upload/attachment/af4d8bef3060e38509804619f73b75ee.docx', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" xss=removed><b><span xss=removed>Online\r\nenvironment is merely an extension of face to face learning environment’,\r\nDiscuss why?</span></b><b><span xss=removed><o></o></span></b></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraph\" xss=removed>&lt;!--[if !supportLists]--&gt;<b><span xss=removed>1.<span xss=removed>       </span></span></b>&lt;!--[endif]--&gt;<b><span xss=removed>Introduction:<o></o></span></b></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" xss=removed><span xss=removed>Online\r\nenvironment is an educational approach, cultural context and physical setting where\r\nthe teaching & learning occur by using ICT (information & communication\r\ntechnologies). Many of the principles of face to face teaching & learning\r\nalso apply to online facilitation, such as <b>principles\r\nof facilitator’s</b> being the <u>guide</u> should allow student to work\r\nthemselves through issues instead of supplying information only; In addition\r\naddress the familiar issues of competition, conflict & responsibilities. E-learning\r\nenvironments are of two types: <b>Purely\r\nonline</b> or <b>Blended </b>(online and\r\nface-to-face). <o></o></span></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpFirst\" xss=removed>&lt;!--[if !supportLists]--&gt;<b><span xss=removed>2.<span xss=removed>       </span></span></b>&lt;!--[endif]--&gt;<b><span xss=removed>Discussion:<o></o></span></b></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" xss=removed>&lt;!--[if !supportLists]--&gt;<span xss=removed>a.<span xss=removed>      \r\n</span></span>&lt;!--[endif]--&gt;<span xss=removed>Blended e-learning is an\r\nextension of face to face learning environment, here online environment and\r\nface-to-face both are used for the learning<o></o></span></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" xss=removed>&lt;!--[if !supportLists]--&gt;<span xss=removed>b.<span xss=removed>     \r\n</span></span>&lt;!--[endif]--&gt;<span xss=removed>Problem based learning (PBL): In\r\ne-learning the PBL may be practiced either as purely <b><u>e-PBL</u></b> or <b><u>Face to\r\nface e-PBL</u></b>. <o></o></span></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" xss=removed><u><span xss=removed>Face to face e-PBL</span></u><span xss=removed>\r\nis an extension of face to face learning environment in online learning.<o></o></span></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" xss=removed>&lt;!--[if !supportLists]--&gt;<span xss=removed>c.<span xss=removed>      \r\n</span></span>&lt;!--[endif]--&gt;<b><span xss=removed>‘Synchronous\r\nformal question and answer in a chat room</span></b><span xss=removed>’ is one way of\r\ne-learning process where the student and faculty meet online as in lecture\r\ntheatre.- an extension of face to face learning environment.<o></o></span></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" xss=removed>&lt;!--[if !supportLists]--&gt;<span xss=removed>d.<span xss=removed>     \r\n</span></span>&lt;!--[endif]--&gt;<b><span xss=removed>‘Formal\r\nclasses in Bulletin board’ </span></b><span xss=removed>is one way of online learning\r\nwhere student may involve in discussion panel session like SGT- an extension of\r\nface to face learning environment.<o></o></span></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" xss=removed>&lt;!--[if !supportLists]--&gt;<span xss=removed>e.<span xss=removed>     \r\n</span></span>&lt;!--[endif]--&gt;<span xss=removed>Audio conferencing using<b> VoIP</b>(Voice over internet protocol) or\r\nTeleconferencing by using Skype, a learner can interact with the teacher, is an\r\nextension of face to face learning environment.<o></o></span></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpLast\" xss=removed>&lt;!--[if !supportLists]--&gt;<span xss=removed>f.<span xss=removed>       \r\n</span></span>&lt;!--[endif]--&gt;<b><span xss=removed>Video\r\nconferencing</span></b><span xss=removed> and <b>Web\r\nconferencing</b>: Here the student and faculty can interact much as live\r\nlecture, or live SGT. Both are the examples of an extension of face to face\r\nlearning environment.<o></o></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" xss=removed><span xss=removed> </span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" xss=removed><b><span xss=removed>Describe the process of  e-learning and its role in CPD?</span></b><span xss=removed><o></o></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" xss=removed><u><span xss=removed>Answer:</span></u><span xss=removed>\r\nProcess of e-learning are structuring the Schedules, Rules & Protocol of\r\nhuman activity involve in e-learning. E-learning contents include teaching\r\nmaterials, reference materials, materials of practice domain & guides.\r\nContents may be created & determined by teacher or student selected or\r\ncommunity supported.<o></o></span></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpFirst\" xss=removed>&lt;!--[if !supportLists]--&gt;<span xss=removed>1.<span xss=removed>       </span></span>&lt;!--[endif]--&gt;<span xss=removed>Process\r\nfor content (two types): Digital materials (websites, books, study guide,\r\nlecture slide,) and course content (syllabi/ Curricula).<o></o></span></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" xss=removed>&lt;!--[if !supportLists]--&gt;<span xss=removed>a.<span xss=removed>      \r\n</span></span>&lt;!--[endif]--&gt;<span xss=removed>Online processing for e<b>-</b>learning activities include <b>participating in</b> <u>online discussion</u>,<b> </b><u>online chatting</u>,<b> </b><u>conferencing</u> (Tele-conferencing,\r\nAudio conferencing, video conferencing).l<o></o></span></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" xss=removed>&lt;!--[if !supportLists]--&gt;<span xss=removed>b.<span xss=removed>     \r\n</span></span>&lt;!--[endif]--&gt;<span xss=removed>Online searching: Accessing\r\ne-learning content (e-journal, e-books); e-portfolios; assessment; exercise to\r\nstimulate thinking.<o></o></span></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" xss=removed>&lt;!--[if !supportLists]--&gt;<span xss=removed>c.<span xss=removed>      \r\n</span></span>&lt;!--[endif]--&gt;<span xss=removed>Processing of offline activities:\r\nInteractive simulation, animation, DVD, Reusable learning material.<o></o></span></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpLast\" xss=removed>&lt;!--[if !supportLists]--&gt;<span xss=removed>d.<span xss=removed>     \r\n</span></span>&lt;!--[endif]--&gt;<span xss=removed>Instant messaging by email, Informal\r\ncourse related discussions.<o></o></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" xss=removed><span xss=removed> </span></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpFirst\" xss=removed>&lt;!--[if !supportLists]--&gt;<span xss=removed>2.<span xss=removed>       </span></span>&lt;!--[endif]--&gt;<span xss=removed>Process\r\nfor supporting logistic & e-administration: <o></o></span></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" xss=removed>&lt;!--[if !supportLists]--&gt;<span xss=removed>a.<span xss=removed>      \r\n</span></span>&lt;!--[endif]--&gt;<span xss=removed>Tracking of content &\r\nparticipant, managing placement, timetable, exam result. <o></o></span></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" xss=removed>&lt;!--[if !supportLists]--&gt;<span xss=removed>b.<span xss=removed>     \r\n</span></span>&lt;!--[endif]--&gt;<span xss=removed>Registration, financing, human\r\nresources, building etc.<o></o></span></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" xss=removed>&lt;!--[if !supportLists]--&gt;<span xss=removed>c.<span xss=removed>      \r\n</span></span>&lt;!--[endif]--&gt;<span xss=removed>Audit, quality assurance &\r\ncompliance, scrutiny.<o></o></span></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" xss=removed>&lt;!--[if !supportLists]--&gt;<span xss=removed>3.<span xss=removed>       </span></span>&lt;!--[endif]--&gt;<span xss=removed>Process\r\nfor assessment: Use of ICT for authoring, delivery, marking, feedback, analysis.<o></o></span></p><p cla