INSERT INTO `assignments_reply` VALUES (155, 116, 'Power point presentation on Bipolar Mood Disorder for undergraduate students', 'Please find the attached file, Assignment 6.', '2018-03-01 07:00:54', 'upload/attachment/b13a305f112af5e4648a9e8dcbce7c20.ppt', '<p>Dear Dr. Nasim Jahan,</p><p>Thanks for timely submission of your assignment. You have done a wonderful job. You have followed more or less the basic norms of PPT. Here I like to put some comments for your assistance to further improve.</p><p>1. You could put the image alone in 1st slide to catch the attention of the learners and ask them what could be today\'s topic?  Topic in 2nd slide. The image is overstretched, so you can stretch the normal pic by putting the cursor at one corner. </p><p>2. You could put objectives and recall items in two different slides and use appear animation with each. </p><p>    Please write the objectives following the rules, like-</p><p>    Students will be able to-</p><p>            define,</p><p>            mention.. etc</p><p>3. Image is hazy. and can use appear animation with both.</p><p>4. You could make 3 slices of the image used by 1st making 3 copies then selecting each and clicking on format pic and selecting crop icon and then cropping each keeping one part alone. Then can put each part separately with appear image. </p><p>5. In slide 5, 6, 7 can use appear animation for better presentation.</p><p>6. In slide 8 have to use indentation after \'severe enough\' for the remaining write up.</p><p>7. Better to high light by using different colour and/or italic/bold. Please don\'t use underline and don\'t put full stop if not a complete sentence.</p><h5>8. Lifetime risk and first-degree relative risk should be written as-  Overall lifetime risk- .. and in first-degree relative risk increases....   .</h5><h5>    Should use bullet points here.</h5><p>9. In 11th slide- heading can be put as, Factors influencing-</p><p>10.In 13th slide- instead of acute treatment it would be better if write treatment in acute condition.</p><h5>Please do the necessary correction and resend the assignment.</h5><p>Enjoy your wonderful effort.</p><p>Best regards</p><p>Dr. Muna</p>', NULL, '2018-03-02 13:47:28', 'F');
INSERT INTO `assignments_reply` VALUES (156, 113, 'Preparation of Power-point presentation ', 'Preparation of Power-point presentation', '2018-03-01 07:07:38', 'upload/attachment/afcac3cef6c548078af235ccbdc17e42.pptx', '<p>Dear Sir,</p><p>Congratulations for taking a keen interest in medical education after having a long teaching experience. You have done a wonderful job in preparing your assignment specially reflecting Gangne\'s nine events of instruction.  Here I like to put some comments for further improvement.</p><p>1. It would be better if you put the 2nd slide first to catch the attention of the class and then welcome them to the tutorial class.</p><p>2. In 3rd slide- don\'t put any full stop.</p><p>3. In 4th slide- can box the recall answers and use appear animations to allow appearing each point one after another and don\'t use full stop on any slide if not a complete sentence.</p><p>4. In 5th slide- no need to use bullets and the images are far apart and hazy.</p><p>5. In 6th slide- you can use slide layout and choose a double box to enclose one theme and one pic in each box. </p><p>6. In 7th slide- heading can be modified as- factors influencing- and you can use appear animation for each factor so that student won\'t see all at a time and you can use the opportunity to get a response from students.</p><p>7. In 9th slide- image is hazy.</p><p>8. In 12th slide- each point is to be put in different slides.</p><p>You have used different entrance animation in different slides which are distracting. I think it is better not to use any entrance animation for the slide itself but appear animation can be used on each slide contents.</p><p>Overall you have done great. It will be highly appreciated if you take the trouble to resubmit after incorporating suggested changes.</p><p>Best regards.</p><p><br></p><p>Muna</p>', NULL, '2018-03-02 14:22:19', 'F');
INSERT INTO `assignments_reply` VALUES (157, 118, 'An effective power point presentation on enzyme', 'An effective power point presentation on enzyme', '2018-03-02 01:41:58', 'upload/attachment/7b76dadfbd22829ac0f9255620a51ba2.pptx', '<p>Dear Dr. Nahar,</p><p>Thank you for your great effort. Indeed you have achieved the goal with a very good ppt presentation which maintained norms. </p><p>Here are some comments to work on for further improvement.</p><p>1. You could have used something to gain the attention of the class in your first slide.</p><p>2. You have used images and graphics efficiently but can use some appear animation to give the students space to sink in the lecture.</p><p>3. In 7th slide, in header box instead of cont.. you could have written the heading of the text.</p><p>4. in 9th slide, you can write substrate concentration in header box. You stretched the graph image too much in 9th, 10th and 11th slide, which made it blurred. Keep the original size and if you want to enlarge then drag from one corner.</p><p>5. In 10th slide, write enzyme concentration in header. A similar correction is to be made in no. 11.</p><p>6. In slide 12 and 13, you used \'enzymes used\' repeatedly. You can use this as common to all sentences.</p><p>Finally your ppt reflected less of Gangne\'s nine events of instruction. For that, you need to put some element to test recall and also to give feedback and/ or can provide a slide with further reading material.</p><p>Thanks again. Keep it up.</p><p>Best regards.</p><p><br></p><p>Dr. Muna</p><p><br></p>', NULL, '2018-03-03 02:23:39', 'F');
INSERT INTO `assignments_reply` VALUES (158, 122, 'Assignment: Please prepare an effective power point presentation (10-12 slides) on a topic you want to teach relevant to your discipline following principles of creating effective ppt and also keeping in mind of Gangne’s nine events of instruction for you', 'Assignment: Please prepare an effective power point presentation (10-12 slides) on a topic you want to teach relevant to your discipline following principles of creating effective ppt and also keeping in mind of Gangne’s nine events of instruction for your presentation.', '2018-03-02 10:00:19', 'upload/attachment/2eae855141c0cf2ee336e0afac63649f.pptx', '<p>Dear fellow,</p><p>Congratulations. You have done a great job. In your ppt you have maintained almost all the basic norms of preparing ppt and also reflected well Gangne\'s nine events of instruction. Here I like to put some points for further improvement.</p><p>1. In 1st slide- instead of 8 images you could have put 4 good quality images.</p><p>2. In 2nd slide-  you can use appear animation on the lecture topic and click on that after asking the students \'what\'s today\'s topic?\'</p><p>3. In 4th slide- Heading can be rephrased as- carbohydrates are...</p><p>    can put appear animation on each important segment of definition</p><p>4. In 7th slide- Heading can be rephrased as- \' classified on the basis of sugar units\'</p><p>    then put the classification. Adequate margin to be kept above.</p><p>5. In 8th slide- Adequate margin to be kept.</p><p>6. In 9th and 10th slides- should not use any full stop unless it is a complete sentence.</p><p>7. in 14th slide please use less number of pics and adequate margin.</p><p>Overall you have achieved what was expected.</p><p>Keep it up.</p><p>Best regards. </p><p>Dr. Muna</p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><br></p>', NULL, '2018-03-02 12:52:50', 'F');
INSERT INTO `assignments_reply` VALUES (159, 114, 'Power-point preparation and presentation', 'Madam,\r\nPlease see the assignment.', '2018-03-02 12:37:02', 'upload/attachment/902804f52301684b20587a79510bdc5e.pptx', '<p>Dear Dr. Masum,</p><p>Thanks for the assignment submission. I am wondering how come you and <span xss=removed>Dr. Shabnam Sarwar Sejooti have submitted the same ppt on the same topic. Please clarify this and you need to resubmit your assignment.</span></p><p><span xss=removed>Thanks again and best regards.</span></p><p>Dr. Muna</p>', NULL, '2018-03-02 14:38:02', 'F');
INSERT INTO `assignments_reply` VALUES (160, 121, 'Urinary Tract Infection(UTI)', 'Madam,\r\n I am attaching PPT', '2018-03-02 01:23:12', 'upload/attachment/2eda24812e99deb969de401da1a710f2.ppt', '<p>Dear Dr. Saha,</p><p>Thank you so much for submitting a neat presentation on ppt. You have followed the basic norms very efficiently and ppt also reflects well Gangne\'s nine events of instruction. </p><p>Here are a few comments for further improvement.</p><p>You could have put the image of 2nd slide on 1st slide in between topic and your name.</p><p>Objectives should be written with action verbs in the following way.. </p><p>\'students would be able to -define, enumerate, list\' etc.</p><p>You have used a case scenario at 13th slide, which would have been better if put at the beginning to gain attention and also to test knowledge basis of students.</p><p>You could have used more images like cystoscopic appearance of cystitis for making the student more interested.</p><p>Finally, you have done a wonderful job. Keep it up.</p><p>Best regards.</p><p>Dr. Muna</p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><br></p>', NULL, '2018-03-04 01:22:55', 'F');
INSERT INTO `assignments_reply` VALUES (161, 126, 'Title of the unit: Power point preparation and presentation', 'Power point preparation and presentation ', '2018-03-02 03:18:24', 'upload/attachment/6a3da8d54290833d2d52c59abf587c41.ppt', '<p>Dear Dr. Irin,</p><p>Thank you for submitting the assignment. You have presented a framework of actual presentation which is not a suitable topic for a lecture.  But you have followed the norms of preparing ppt efficiently and also reflected Gangne\'s nine events of instruction well. </p><p>Here are a few comments for further improvement.</p><p>1.  Learning objectives should be written with action verbs like \'students will be able to define\' etc.</p><p>2. Before describing types you need to define breech. </p><p>3. On 7th slide sequence to be maintained. Pelvic examination and then USG.</p><p>4. No. 11 slide needs margin before the text.</p><p>5. You need to use a good quality image to have a better visual from behind.</p><p>Finally, you have done a wonderful job.</p><p>Keep going.</p><p>Best regards.</p><p>Dr. Muna</p><p><br></p><p><br></p>', NULL, '2018-03-04 02:17:25', 'F');
INSERT INTO `assignments_reply` VALUES (162, 115, 'Preparation an effective power point presentation on acute kidney injury following principles of creating effective ppt and keeping in mind of Gangne’s nine events of instruction', 'Madam,\r\nAssalamualaikum.\r\nAttaching the assignment herewith on \"AKI\".\r\n\r\nMuhammad Abdur Rahim', '2018-03-02 03:50:48', 'upload/attachment/ec3eb26236038c23a89c5bf04a5c9b3a.pptx', '<p>Dear Dr. Rahim,</p><p>Thanks for submission of the assignment. You have prepared the ppt following almost all norms and reflected very well the Gangne\'s nine events of instruction. </p><p>Only a few comments for further improvement are-</p><p>you can put the 2nd slide first to gain the attention of the class and also to find out their knowledge level.</p><p>You can use one or two images of dialysis or patient\'s pic to increase interest. </p><p>In 4th slide, you can use appear animation with each renal function which will give you an opportunity to assess students physiology knowledge.</p><p>In the 6th slide, the image used won\'t be clearly readable from behind. You can fragment the slide content into 3 and also can use images.</p><p>In 9th, 10th, 11th slide, you can use appear animation to deliver the information slowly.</p><p>Finally, I like to congratulate you for providing further reading slide.</p><p>Thanks again for a good effort and wonderful job.</p><p>Keep continuing.</p><p>Best regards.</p><p>Dr. Muna</p><p><br></p>', NULL, '2018-03-02 23:10:53', 'F');
INSERT INTO `assignments_reply` VALUES (163, 123, 'Please prepare an effective power point presentation (10-12 slides) on a topic you want to teach relevant to your discipline following principles of creating effective ppt and also keeping in mind of Gangne’s nine events of instruction for your presentati', '', '2018-03-02 07:00:48', 'upload/attachment/dc09f5b264025572268f034bbab28715.ppt', '<p>Dear Dr. Taslima,</p><p>Thank you for submitting your assignment.  you have done a great job and your ppt reflects basic norms as well as Gangn\'s nine events of instruction.</p><p>Here are a few comments for further improvement.</p><p>1. You need to be very careful regarding color contrast. Test color on the background you have chosen failed to show the appeal. It will be very hard for the students from back to clearly read the slides.</p><p>2. It would have been better if you have put the image on 3rd slide with the 1st question on 1st slide. It would have helped you to gain the attention of the students.</p><p>3. On all slides you have to keep an adequate margin for a better look and clear readability.</p><p>4. You could have used appear animation on 9th slide.</p><p>Good job is done. Keep it up.</p><p>Best regards.</p><p>Dr. Muna</p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p>2.</p>', NULL, '2018-03-04 02:34:17', 'F');
INSERT INTO `assignments_reply` VALUES (164, 120, 'SAM for lecture', '', '2018-03-02 07:32:04', 'upload/attachment/32c1f7f79ff73e57dd8d4378b5a88d61.ppt', '<p>Dear Dr. Shaheen,</p><p>You have done a great job preparing ppt following the norms and your ppt reflects well Gangne\'s nine events of instruction. Only a few comments for further assistance as follows-</p><p>In 2nd slide, I haven\'t understood what is the animation and what for?</p><p>In 6th slide, heading could be modified as \'calculating weight and height using graph chart\', then you could have more space to increase the size of the chart image.</p><p>In 7th slide you could have used appear animation with each point so that whole flowchart won\'t be visualized at a time.</p><p>Overall your ppt is really a good one. keep it up.</p><p>Best regards.</p><p>Dr. Muna</p>', NULL, '2018-03-04 00:59:03', 'F');
INSERT INTO `assignments_reply` VALUES (165, 127, 'Assignment: Please prepare an effective power point presentation (10-12 slides) on a topic you want to teach relevant to your discipline following principles of creating effective ppt and also keeping in mind of Gangne’s nine events of instruction for you', 'Madam, a\r\nAsssalamualaikum. Here I am submitting my assignment as attachment for your review please.\r\nThanks.\r\nA.E.MD.ABDUL WASEY', '2018-03-02 07:47:52', 'upload/attachment/e025ff83b8bfe86ef91cf9c20d85ac54.pptx', '<h5>Dear Dr. Wasey,</h5><p>Indeed a great job is done.  Your assignment was to prepare a presentation with 10-12 slides, but you have prepared a whole lecture! Wonderful!</p><p>Here are a few comments for your assistance to improve further.</p><p>1. In 1st slide, you can put a case scenario and it should not contain any text straight away. You need to introduce yourself.</p><p>2. In 2nd slide, you need to keep clear margin all around text and try to avoid same action verb, like \' advise relevant investigations. You should avoid mentioning appendicitis in all sentences.</p><p>3. in 6th slide, no need to write \'Etiology\' again as a subheading. It is better to use indentation in 2nd segment rather than different bullets.</p><p>4.  in 8th slide and also in other slides, no need to write \'there is\'. As it is better to use phrases rather than complete sentences.</p><p>5. In 10th and 11th slides, you need to keep an adequate clear margin all around the images used.</p><p>6. In 12th slide, better heading will be \'physical examination findings\' or \'physical features\'.</p><p>7. In slide 15 and 16, you could have used appear animation with all D/Ds under each heading, not with the whole segment.</p><h5>8. In 17th slide, instead of what you have written if you rephrase as \' no single investigation can diagnose\', how does it sound?</h5><h5>9. In 19th slide, please rephrase the sentences to make them short and don\'t repeat in the text what you have written in heading. </h5><p>Finally, you have used images and animation, effectively. So, thanks again.</p><p>Keep it up.</p><p>Best regards.</p><p>Dr. Muna</p><h5><br></h5><p><font face=\"Arial\"><span xss=removed><br></span></font></p>', NULL, '2018-03-03 00:57:01', 'F');
INSERT INTO `assignments_reply` VALUES (166, 128, 'Assignment on power point preparation', '', '2018-03-02 10:17:48', 'upload/attachment/00c612aeda8cc362dfabec38818ab1d9.pptx', '<p>Dear Dr. Maruf Raza,</p><p>Here are some points to further work on.</p><p>1. in 3rd slide, Heading should be Neoplasm, and text should start from \'according to..\'</p><p>2. In 4th slide, Heading should be \'benign neoplasm\' instead of tumour as you didn\'t mention that both words are used interchangeably. In no. 1 bullet, you can omit \'the tumour\'s\'. You can also use an image of any benign neoplasm.</p><p>3. Similar and grammatical correction needed in 5th slide.</p><p>4. In 6th slide, please omit \'metastasis is\' from definition and metastasis from no.1 bullet.</p><p>5. In slide 7, 9 and 10, omit the full stops as these are not complete sentences. in slide 10 1st bullet is a repetition of the previous slide and can omit the last segment of 3rd bullet starting from \'for the.. .</p><p>6. In slide 11, please omit \'it is\' and can use a. and b. instead of 1), and 2) and remove all full stops.</p><p>7. Your last slide needs rephrasing to make all 3 points short. </p><p>8. Lastly, you could have used more images and can conclude with something thought-provoking. </p><p>Overall your effort is appreciable and  I hope you will enjoy creating your own presentation more.</p><p>Best regards.</p><p>Dr. Muna</p><p><br></p><p><br></p>', NULL, '2018-03-03 01:32:17', 'F');
INSERT INTO `assignments_reply` VALUES (167, 124, 'Prepare an effective power point presentation (10-12 slides) on a topic want to teach relevant to your discipline following principles of creating effective PPT and also keeping in mind of Gagne\'s nine events of instruction.', '', '2018-03-02 10:36:44', 'upload/attachment/19f271fc8840abf02ce7fea9ab135698.PPT', '<p>Dear Dr. Rahman,</p><p>Sorry for late feedback as we have encountered some technological problem. You have done a great job preparing a good ppt following norms. Thanks for keeping in mind Gangne\'s nine events of instruction.</p><p>Here are a few comments on your assistance for further improvement.</p><p>1. To gain the attention of the class You could have put a case scenario or problem faced during pleural fluid aspiration. </p><p>2. In objective writing little correction is needed. You have to follow the norms of objective writing. Objective of the session will be like this.. \' at the end of the session ( though you need not write this portion, only can tell), students will be able to-- maintain accuracy and...., perform efficiently USG guided FNAC...\'</p><p>3. In 4th slide, if you have written \'USG guided Pleural fluid aspiration\' instead of Introduction in the heading. Don\'t put any full stop unless it is a complete sentence.</p><p>4. Images you have used are good but you can separate each by using Format pics and crop options and use appear animation for each.</p><p>Overall your presentation fulfilled our expectations. Keep it up. </p><p>Best regards.</p><p>Dr. Muna</p><p><br></p>', NULL, '2018-03-06 10:16:37', 'F');
INSERT INTO `assignments_reply` VALUES (168, 112, 'Torsion Of The Testes ', '', '2018-03-02 10:55:29', 'upload/attachment/dcbd5377f1b1cea9e3139fdd09c9ba5c.pptx', '<p>Dear Dr. Haque,</p><p>Thanks for the submission of the assignment. you have done a wonderful job by following almost all basic rules of preparing ppt. Your ppt also reflects well Gangne\'s nine events of instruction.</p><p>Here are a few points for further improvement.</p><p>In first slide, you need not write  \'let me tell a story\' which you can tell.</p><p>Contrast is very important for clear visibility from the back of the class. You could have used a dark blue or white background, preferably dark one to project clearly the images you used.</p><p>You could have used \'appear animation\' in some of your slides especially on no. 9  to deliver the contents one after another and which will give you an opportunity to assess students level of knowledge and understanding.</p><p>Adding one more slide stating further reading or resources will help the students much.</p><p>Well done. keep it up.</p><p>Best regards.</p><p><br></p><p>Dr. Muna</p><p><br></p>', NULL, '2018-03-02 23:36:37', 'F');
INSERT INTO `assignments_reply` VALUES (169, 131, 'An effective power point presentation on Acute Angle Closure Glaucoma', '', '2018-03-02 11:27:22', 'upload/attachment/b8264e25fff36d178bbc89b26a7c9f5c.pptx', '<p>Dear Dr. Purobi,</p><p>Thanks for your great effort. You have done a wonderful job following almost all basic rules of preparing ppt.</p><p>Here are some points for your assistance to improve further.</p><p>You can put the 2nd slide first to get the attention of the class.</p><p>In the objective slide 3rd bullet, it would be better to write as- to examine the eye and to suggest relevant investigations.</p><p>In 4th slide, 3rd bullet should be the second and use only the phrases not the whole sentence and please don\'t underline. To highlight using a different color or bold or italic is a good option.</p><p>5th slide doesn\'t need any heading.</p><p>In 6th slide, the image you have used is not a good one.  you can make a table by yourself using a better color combination and with good fonts.</p><p>In 7th, 8th and 9th slides, you can use appear animation to slowly deliver the contents and which can give you an opportunity to test students\' synthesizing ability.</p><p>In 10th slide, you can put the text a little more down for a better look.</p><p>In 11th slide, you can put a title before the actual management and use indentation. So in total, there would be 3 headings in the text.</p><p>Finally, you could have added another slide with further reading to help the students.</p><p><br></p><p>Overall you have done a great job.</p><p>Keep it up.</p><p>Best regards</p><p>Dr. Muna</p>', NULL, '2018-03-03 00:07:31', 'F');
INSERT INTO `assignments_reply` VALUES (170, 125, 'Power point preparation and presentation', 'power point preparation and presentation', '2018-03-03 12:35:11', 'upload/attachment/4f33a1a298a6922e546443f44faa81c5.pptx', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `assignments_reply` VALUES (171, 114, 'Power point preperation', 'Madam,\r\nSorry for late reply. First i attempted to work on white background then switched to others, but accidentally during attachment from desktop another ppt has wrongly attached.\r\nPlease see the attachment for my PPT,', '2018-03-03 01:56:56', 'upload/attachment/d6cbb89e35cb2ac0ee3bfee17dcff2f1.pptx', '<p>Dear Dr. Masum,</p><p>Thanks for resubmission. Your this presentation is a good one with the reflection of following norms of ppt and Gangne\'s nine events of instruction.</p><p>Here are few comments for further improvement.</p><p>1. In your 1st slide, you have put a good pic to gain the attention of students but the caption is to be modified to allow the students to guess what is that and use appear animation with a caption saying Arsenicosis.</p><p>2. In 2nd slide, you can use appear animation with the topic title after asking students how can we measure arsenicosis.</p><p>3. You have to put 4th slide 1st then 3rd slide to maintain sequence ie first the investigation then what instrument is used.</p><p>4. You have mixed fonts, on some slides Verdana, on some Arial, again on some Times new roman.  Please use only  San serif fonts and one type in one ppt. You have also used shade which decreases readability.</p><p>5. In 7th slide, you have placed too much text. You can easily reduce by omitting all articles and the unnecessary portion which you can present orally. </p><p>6. Be careful about spellings and Keep adequate margin around all images or graphics used.</p><p>7. Finally, try to wrap up the presentation with something like \'take home message or resources for further reading\'.</p><p>Your effort is appreciable. Keep it up.</p><p>Best regards<br></p><p>Dr. Muna</p><p><br></p>', NULL, '2018-03-06 11:28:23', 'F');
INSERT INTO `assignments_reply` VALUES (172, 113, 'PPT', 'PPT', '2018-03-03 03:45:47', 'upload/attachment/122a02ccdbb4e37998b924df5f9ea383.pptx', '<p>Sir,</p><p>I am really impressed observing your enthusiasm. Much improved from previous one and I hope with time you will excel. We have so many things to learn from you.</p><p>May Allah bless you with good health and long life to continue grooming batches of students.</p><p>Best regards.</p><p>Muna</p><p><br></p>', NULL, '2018-03-05 01:39:11', 'F');
