INSERT INTO `assignments_reply` VALUES (210, 156, ' Prepare a study guide of a topic of your discipline ', 'Assignment \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nCertificate in Medical Education (CMEd)\r\nBIRDEM Academy\r\nModule: Instructional design \r\nUnit name: Study guide and hand out\r\nCode: IMD4\r\n\r\n                                                                            Submitted by-\r\n                                               Shudhanshu kumar saha\r\n         Email- shudhanshukumarsaha@gmail.com\r\n        Cell 01759961995\r\n\r\n A study guide is an educational tool or part of self instructional package, usually presented in the form of printed notes, produced and designed for students to use independently .It contains some of the content of curriculum as core and indicates what should be learned and how can be learned. In addition, study guide encourage students to take more responsibility for their own learning and students can use the various resources available on a given topic that is listed in the study guide.\r\n\r\nContent of study guide-\r\n Objectives of the course\r\n List of content\r\n Teaching methods to be used\r\n Self assessment exercise\r\n Resource available\r\nRoles of study guide:\r\n Assisting in the management of student learning\r\n Providing a focus for student activities related to learning\r\n Providing information to the subject\r\n\r\nSo, study guide do \r\n Framework on which student can build own understanding\r\n Student take responsibility of their own learning \r\n\r\nAssignment Topic: - Prepare a study guide of a topic of your discipline emphasis on following\r\n Learning objective\r\n Introduction\r\n Teaching learning methods\r\n Learning material and \r\n self-assessment exercise \r\n\r\nTopic- Acute kidney injury (AKI)\r\nLearning objective-\r\n Define AKI \r\n Mention etiology of AKI \r\n Evaluate clinical and laboratory investigation\r\n Mention complications of AKI\r\n Principles of management and \r\n Prognosis\r\n\r\nIntroduction: - AKI is a common problem in community. Mounting evidence suggests that acute, relatively mild injury to the kidney or impairment of kidney function, manifest by change in urine output and blood chemistries, portend serious clinical consequences so,\r\n AKI may be defined as presence of one or more of following three:\r\n1. Rise of serum creatinine >0.3 mg/dl in 48-h\r\n2. Rise of serum creatinine >1.5 times of base-line in 7 days\r\n3. Urine output <0>0.3 mg/dl in 48-h\r\n      b). Rise of serum creatinine >1.5 times of base-line in 7 days\r\n      c). Urine output <0>0.5 ml/kg/h for 6 hours\r\n\r\n', '2018-03-16 04:18:18', 'upload/attachment/77a15b92e1c6b76bef8208e5f24c6e79.docx', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" align=\"center\" xss=removed><br></p>', 'upload/attachment/6ac35134d26797c48579b5e092dab13f.docx', '2018-03-18 11:28:06', 'F');
