INSERT INTO `assignments_reply` VALUES (230, 191, 'Task:   Define teaching & learning.  Enumerate the strategies that will enhance effective learning  Enlist the conditions of learning  Enlist the roles of a teacher.   What are the types of clinical teaching?  Describe the educational objectives tha', 'Assignment \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nCertificate in Medical Education (CMEd)\r\nBIRDEM Academy\r\nModule: Teaching learning \r\nUnit name: Principles of teaching and learning and teaching methods\r\n                                                 Code: M3TL1\r\n\r\n \r\n                                                    Submitted by-\r\n                                              Shudhanshu kumar saha\r\n                                         Email- shudhanshukumarsaha@gmail.com\r\n Cell 01759961995\r\n\r\n\r\nTask: \r\n Define teaching & learning.\r\n Enumerate the strategies that will enhance effective learning\r\n Enlist the conditions of learning\r\n Enlist the roles of a teacher. \r\n What are the types of clinical teaching?\r\n Describe the educational objectives that can be achieved in bed side teaching.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nIntroduction: Education is a process the chief goal of which is to bring about changes in human behavior. Learning is a process resulting in some modification relatively permanent of the behavior, in the way of thinking, feeling and doing of the learner. Teaching is an organized communication and interactive process concerned with learning to nurture thinking ability.\r\n\r\nTeaching-In its generic form is concerned with providing student with opportunities to learn, or it may be defined as an organized communication between the teacher and the students\r\nPurpose of teaching- \r\n1. To facilitate learning \r\n2. Acquire and retain knowledge\r\n3. Use knowledge to understand, analyze, synthesis and evaluate\r\n4. Achieve skills\r\n5. Develop attitude\r\n\r\nLearning:\r\nLearning is a continuous process\r\nResulting in some modification in way of thinking, feeling and doing\r\nConstructive and active process that result in change in behavior\r\nTaking new information, build it on existing knowledge\r\nEstablishing connection within and between units of knowledge\r\n\r\nEffective learning: It becomes effective when the objectives are clearly understood by the students. In addition, correct practice and timely and appropriate feedback from the teachers makes learning more effective so, strategies for effective learning are\r\n1. Identify and articulate clear learning objective\r\n2. Provide instructions through large or small group teaching or individually\r\n3. Use instructional methods\r\n4. Engage all students actively\r\n5. Assess and monitor continuously\r\n6. Provide relevant and continuous feedback\r\n7. Support learner to be an independent learner\r\nCondition of learning:\r\nFollowing atmosphere is helpful for facilating learning- \r\n1. Encourage people to be active\r\n2. Emphasize the personal nature of learning\r\n3. Accept that difference is desirable\r\n4. Recognize the people’s right to make mistake\r\n5. Tolerates Imperceptions \r\n6. Encourages openness of self and trust in self\r\n7. Make people feel respected and accepted\r\n8. Facilitate discovery\r\n9. Puts emphasis on self-evaluation and cooperation\r\n10. Permits confrontation\r\n\r\nRole of a teacher:\r\nIn clinical teaching the teacher and the students come in contact with each other with a prior set of knowledge, experience and expectations. It is vital for the teacher to know the learners existing knowledge and identify the deficiency so, a good teacher should have 12 roles for an effective clinical teaching-\r\n1. Information provider during lecture\r\n2. Information provider in clinical/ practical teaching\r\n3. Role model in teaching\r\n4. Role model in job\r\n5. Teacher acts as learning facilator\r\n6. Act as a mentor\r\n7. Teachers are assessors for student\r\n8. Assessor for curriculum\r\n9. Teachers are planner for curriculum\r\n10. Planner for course\r\n11. Teachers are study guide producer\r\n12. Teachers are resource material creator\r\n     \r\n\r\nClinical teaching: Teaching learning involving patient and their problems\r\nThree types:\r\n1. Bed side teaching\r\n2. Teaching in clinical skill center\r\n3. Ambulatory care teaching\r\n\r\nEducational objectives:\r\n1. Clinical skill\r\n2. Communication skill\r\n3. Clinical reasoning\r\n4. Practical procedure like CV line, CPR, Venipuncture, catheterization\r\n5. Patient investigation and management\r\n6. Data interpretation and retrieval\r\n7. Professional skill- role model for professional behavior\r\n8. Attitude and ethics\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n', '2018-03-30 08:18:23', 'upload/attachment/57391b621454ff12820c57ac650f778f.docx', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
