INSERT INTO `assignments_reply` VALUES (248, 193, 'Assignment of M3 U 2 1. You are assigned to organize a daylong workshop on Medical education for 20 participants. a. Prepare a pre-workshop plan b. How will you run the workshop( Write Schedule) c. Write your plan of post workshop evaluation meeting. ', 'Module: 3 Teaching-learning\r\nAssignment of M3 U2 \r\nFellow ID: 181020\r\nWorkshop is a common educational format for transmitting information and promoting skill acquisition. Workshops are teaching and learning arrangements, usually in small groups, that are structured to produce active participation in learning. Traditionally, workshops provided participants with some opportunity to practice skills and receive feedback.\r\na) Pre-workshop plan-\r\n1) Selection of topic and the learning objectives of the workshop will be specified-\r\nEvery decisions that are taken about the workshop will depend on objectives for the learner and the success will be measured against its objectives. It is also useful to specify the performance levels and the conditions for each learning objective. A day long workshop may provide opportunity for participants to share ideas, experiences, and understanding on a topic if objectives are clearly specified.\r\n2) We have to find out who will be the participants of the workshop-  \r\nWe have to determine who the participants will be. What is their knowledge of the topic? What is their previous experience with this subject matter? What are their needs and expectations? By informing all these along with our topic and objectives, we can send e-mail to different medical colleges for registration. \r\n3) Selection of venue-\r\nVenue will be convenient and comfortable for all- participants and speakers. It should be spacious with appropriate light, power supply, generator facilities, free internet facilities, sound proofed along with other necessary facilities.\r\n4) Seating arrangement\r\nCircular seating arrangements foster sharing of power and interaction between members. Long tables with the teacher at one end tend to concentrate control in the teacher and reduce the tendency for interaction among participants. \r\n\r\n\r\n5)  Selection and management of time schedule of resource persons and speakers-\r\nSelection of qualified resource persons, speakers and anchor will be done according to the topic and availability of their time schedules.\r\n6) Fixation of date of workshop-\r\nDate of workshop is fixed according to the availability of venue and schedule of resource persons.\r\n7) Well organized Program schedule, Materials and Handouts-\r\nThey should be well organized, carefully written and targeted for the participants. These can be kept in a file along with pen drive, pen and writing pad 1 hour before the workshop on the seating place of the participants.\r\n8)  Determination of teaching method and design the appropriate workshop activities-\r\nOnce the objectives of the teaching session are clarified, then we have to choose the teaching method that will best meet our overall goals. A number of methods can be used to involve a group in active learning. These include lectures, small group teaching, case discussions, role plays and simulations, and opportunities for practising specific skills. Workshops should encourage problem-solving and/or skill acquisition.\r\n9) Instructional materials should be checked-\r\nLaptops and related materials for power point presentation should be checked. Fumbling with equipment wastes time. It should be ensured that there are white board markers, pens for flip chart writing and tape if we want to hang some sheets.\r\n10) Preparation of Pre workshop, Post work shop evaluation questionnaire and Feedback form on workshop-\r\nThese should be done very carefully.\r\n11) Timing-\r\nIt is important but difficult to keep schedule in track of time. Appointing a timekeeper can be considered. Ten to twenty percent more time can be added for each activities. Real activities usually take longer time than the planned ones.\r\n12) Budget-  Amount and source of budget should be fixed.\r\nb) Schedule of workshop on\r\nMedical Education\r\nDate -\r\nVenue\r\n\r\n\r\nSerial No. Time Topic Resource person\r\n1 8.00 AM - 9.00 AM Inauguration ceremony and Ice breaking \r\n2 9.00 AM - 9:30 AM Pre test \r\n     3 9.30 AM - 10:15 AM Educational objectives and domain of learning Name of resource person\r\n    4 10.15 AM - 10:45 AM Tea break \r\n    5 10.45 AM - 11:30 AM Preparing Power Point presentation Name of the resource person\r\n    6 11.30 AM – 12.15 PM Interactive large group teaching Name of the resource person\r\n    7 12.15 PM – 1.00 PM Small group teaching  Name of the resource person\r\n    8 1.00 PM – 1.45 PM Prayer and lunch \r\n    9 1.45 PM – 2.30 PM Group work (5 groups, 4 participants in each group)  By all participants\r\n   10 2.30 PM – 3.30 PM Presentation and feed back on group work \r\n   11 3.30 PM – 4.00 PM Post test evaluation and participant’s feedback on workshop by questionnaire \r\n   12 4.00 PM - 4.15 PM Tea break \r\n   13 4.15 PM- 4.45 PM Certificate distribution, closing session and thanks giving \r\n   14 4.45 PM – 5.00 PM Photo session \r\n\r\n\r\nC) Plan of post workshop evaluation meeting-\r\nJust like planning the workshop design, the evaluation of the workshop focuses on the goals for the workshop and how effectively the goals for the workshop are met. Post workshop evaluation meeting will be held by the organizers and conveners as early as possible after the ending of work shop. \r\nIn the workshop evaluation meeting- We have to do the following things-\r\n• Development of a post-workshop evaluation summary that includes the weak points and success of workshop, information from the feedback form on workshop \r\n• Collection of participant’s action plan after the workshop \r\n• Collection of convener’s observations.\r\n• Planning of a post-workshop follow up survey of participants that focuses on action plan responses.\r\n• Finally, bringing participants back together for a second workshop can enhance impact \r\nAttendance and satisfaction of the participants are usually accepted as evidence by administrators and workshop planners of the successfulness of a workshop. \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n', '2018-04-06 10:08:35', 'upload/attachment/6ba272cd217a8e6092ca8009ed0de6ef.doc', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `assignments_reply` VALUES (249, 211, 'Task: You are assigned to organize a day long workshop on Medical education for 20 participants.   Prepare a pre-workshop plan  How will you run the workshop   Write your plan of post workshop evaluation meeting', '   Certificate in Medical Education (CMEd)\r\nBIRDEM Academy\r\nModule: Teaching learning \r\nUnit name: Small group teaching and clinical teaching\r\n                                                 Code: M3Tl2\r\n\r\n \r\n                                                    Submitted by-\r\n                                              Shudhanshu kumar saha\r\n                                         Email- shudhanshukumarsaha@gmail.com\r\n Cell 01759961995\r\n\r\nTask: You are assigned to organize a day long workshop on Medical education for 20 participants.\r\n\r\n Prepare a pre-workshop plan\r\n How will you run the workshop \r\n Write your plan of post workshop evaluation meeting\r\n\r\n.    \r\n\r\nIntroduction:\r\n\r\nWorkshop is a successful way in providing on opportunities for individuals developing gateway to come together and interact.\r\nRegular organization of workshop with addition of new advances in medical educations would be highly beneficial to improve teaching learning skill of medical teacher and to acquire new knowledge and skills.\r\n\r\nPre- workshop plan-\r\n\r\nAim and objective of workshop- Design the learning objective. Objective of the course need to be communicated to students as well as tutor\r\nInstructional method- Prepare contents of  teaching manual, which is composed of a core patient (summary of patients with a major disease), learning objective, case scenario, questions for  group discussion , teaching guide and references for all discipline\r\nSelect a coordinator- Form a core group from representative department and discuss individual responsibility and other relevant issue, as negotiation among disciplines is very essential\r\nPrepare a conceptual framework for planning and implementing integration and communicate with students and teaching staff\r\nManpower- Large member of teaching staff/ tutor familiar with facilitating workshop is required. Tutor need to acquire some basic expertise on teaching. Appropriate staff development programs should be available to meet the needs of the tutor\r\nPhysical:\r\nRoom- A suitable room of appropriate size is required which should be noise free and comfortable with adequate space\r\nArrangement- Requires suitable accommodation and allows chair to be set out in such a way that face to face interaction possible.\r\nMaterial- flipchart, overhead projector, patient, model, books study guide as learning material\r\n\r\nFollowing steps to be followed for smooth running of workshop:\r\n\r\nLesson plan-\r\nForming: Allow adequate introduction that relaxes and introduces the member of the group. Tension is also reduced among group.\r\nNorming: Establish ground rules to attain proper educational climate, setting of behavior and respect to other are essential. Contribution should also be received positively\r\nBriefing: To ensure that the student understand the task and procedure.\r\nFacilitate the learning to achieve the task: Tutor should facilate the learning and help the student become more self-reliant and independent. Tutor also helps students understanding of principles and concept and finally summarizes the discussion\r\nDebriefing the group on the activity: During debriefing constructive feedback may be given focusing on the good points fast; teacher also leads a discussion and provide the class member to demonstrate what they have learned. Learner must state the concepts learned in a clear and concise manner and integrate them appropriately with related knowledge and finally references for further reading\r\n\r\nEvaluate the success of session:\r\nEvaluation is an integral part of workshop. As with any other teaching method it is important to evaluate the success of session. There are two aspects of evaluation- achievement and quality. Informal evaluation can be done for each and every session by asking question to the students as well as by allowing them to ask questions. The formative assessment can be done at the end of the course\r\nRegular evaluation is essential to improve the quality or effectiveness of such program, which is usually measured by outcome such as paticipitants general reaction about the program or the knowledge gained from it\r\nContents of evaluation\r\n Communication skills\r\n Organization skills \r\n Enthusiasm \r\n Flexibility\r\n Attitude towards workshop\r\n Participant’s interaction\r\n Encouragement of the participant\r\n Knowledge of the subject Clarity of presentation\r\n Course difficulty\r\n Fairness of grading and examination\r\n\r\nEvaluation instruments: At the end of workshop, participants  are requested to complete a survey to evaluate the information received, the clarity of the workshop goals, the quality of presentation, instruction and workshop activity and then overall impressions on the events. Based on this feedback, the workshop is a success when the activities averaged greater than 4 on a scale of 1 to 5\r\n\r\n\r\nAction plan: \r\nThere should be an action plan activity at the close of the workshop. Evaluation formal or informal is pointless if no change in practice results .Competent evaluation will always identify the areas for improvement. Reflection cannot be effective in isolation. It should be on going and an integral part of any teaching practice.\r\n\r\nSample of workshop evaluation format (Your valuable comment will make us improve. Thanks)\r\nWorkshop name----------\r\nTraining location------\r\nParticipants Name------\r\nDate\r\nDesignation\r\nDepartment\r\nName of institute\r\nLength of service--------------year\r\nLength of experience----------------year\r\n\r\nInstruction:\r\n\r\n Please circle your response to the items. Please rate different aspects of the workshop on a 1to 5 point scale \r\n1= strongly disagree, or the lowest, most negative impression\r\n2= Disagree\r\n3= neither agree nor disagree or no adequate impression\r\n4= Agree\r\n5= Strongly agree or highest, most positive impression \r\n \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n \r\n', '2018-04-06 11:26:51', 'upload/attachment/9bf395aa4e035cd805e2904760ab2503.docx', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
